Package: sconjoint
Title: Structural Deep-Learning Estimation for Conjoint Experiments
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Avidit", "Acharya", role = "aut"),
    person("Jens", "Hainmueller", role = "aut"),
    person("Yiqing", "Xu", , "yiqingxu@stanford.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Implements the structural deep-learning estimator for
    forced-choice conjoint experiments of Acharya, Hainmueller, and Xu
    (2026), which embeds a deep neural network in a random utility logit
    so that preference parameters vary flexibly with respondent
    characteristics. Provides double/debiased machine-learning inference
    with cross-fitting clustered at the respondent level, and a full set
    of structural quantities including marginal rates of substitution,
    counterfactual choice probabilities, compensating differentials,
    consumer surplus, attribute importance, preference polarization, and
    preference clustering. Builds on 'torch' for the deep-learning
    backend.
